The paper discusses the use of monetary incentives in community-based question answering (CQA) services, which involves social interactions and user engagement. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other possible sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as the paper also touches upon topics such as user behavior, market dynamics, and search algorithms.
